<hl>
<seg id=1> Supporting countries, Japan, Australia, New Zealand and Korea: the US has no other choice </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Tokyo integrated news)Japan, Australis, New Zealand and Korea supported "Operation Desert Fox", by saying that the US had no other choice. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi says Japan support the air raid and urged Bagdad to unconditionally accept UN's arms inspection. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Statement issued by Obuchi said that, Iraq gave inadequate cooperation after the resumption of the arms inspection program. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> "Due to the momentum of past state of affairs, Japan supports the US and UK to conduct this operation." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Korea also expressed its position on supporting the united air raid by the US and Britain. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Australia Prime Minister Howard said that, he believed that the US-UK operation against Iraq is the only choice of the two countries, after he read the report of Butler, the chief of the UN arms inspection delegation. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> French and Germany expressed their regrets and sorrow. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> New Zealand Prime Minister Shipley also issued a special statement, saying that country in the world could not sit by and let Sadam keep on violating the UN resolution. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> In addition, French regretted that the US and UK were forced to take this operation. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=11> French foreign ministry said that, the Iraqi leader refused to cooperate with the UN and caused this regretable consequence. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> Germany was distressed for the military operation. German government spokesman pointed out that, German had warned Iraq that the international community would not stand by and do nothing to Iraq if it voilated the UN resolution. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
